<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-253-448  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 253 448.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 14 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Aussie text retrieval software launched overseas.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Atkins, Gavin.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Odyssey Development (contracts)Regis McKenna Inc. (contracts).andO;Product:   ISYS (Search software) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersContractsMarketing StrategySearching.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AUSSIE TEXT RETRIEVAL SOFTWARE LAUNCHED OVERSEAS SYDNEY, AUSTRALIA, 1989 NOV8 (NB) -- Odyssey Development is turning its attention to overseas marketsnow that its text retrieval software system ISYS has become the most popularpackage of its type in Australia after only 12 months in the marketplace.andM;Odyssey recently employed the Palo Alto-based Regis McKenna Inc., or RMI, tolook after the company's introduction in the US.andP;  Managing Director ofOdyssey Mark Reiss said that RMI's brief was to find a US partner for Odysseyto publish ISYS on an international basis.andM;&quot;We have looked carefully at our international options and decided that,although we could raise enough capital to launch in the US, we do not havethe experience required to take such a risk by ourselves.andP;  We have thereforechosen to take the lower risk option of having one of the major softwarepublishers market our product for us.andP;  Discussions are underway with threemajor US companies and we hope to make an announcement soon,&quot; he said.andM;ISYS allows PC users to search for words and phrases on either a stand-alonePC or LAN which can be retrieved from any one of 25 different word processorfile formats.andM;(Gavin Atkins/19891108)</TEXT></DOC>